bit_field.name: RoTK0_EN
bit_field.description: RoT Key 0 enable. 00 - Invalid 01 - Enabled 10, 11 - Key revoked

bit_field.name: RoTK1_EN
bit_field.description: RoT Key 1 enable. 00 - Invalid 01 - Enabled 10, 11 - Key revoked

bit_field.name: RoTK2_EN
bit_field.description: RoT Key 2 enable. 00 - Invalid 01 - Enabled 10, 11 - Key revoked

bit_field.name: RoTK3_EN
bit_field.description: RoT Key 3 enable. 00 - Invalid 01 - Enabled 10, 11 - Key revoked

register.name: DCFG_CC_SOCU_PIN
register.description: With TZ-M, the part can be sold by level 1 customers (secure code developer) to level-2 customers who develops non-secure code only. - In this scenario, or easy of development, Level-I customer releases the part to always allow non-secure debug. - To allow level-2 customers to further seal the part DCFG_CC_SOCU_NS is used. - ROM will use this word to further restrict the debug access.

bit_field.name: CPU1_DBGEN
bit_field.description: CPU1 (Micro cortex M33) invasive debug enable

bit_field.name: CPU1_NIDEN
bit_field.description: CPU1 (Micro cortex M33) non-invasive debug enable

bit_field.name: UUID_CHECK
bit_field.description: Enforce UUID match during Debug authentication.

register.name: DCFG_CC_SOCU_DFLT
register.description: With TZ-M, the part can be sold by level 1 customers (secure code developer) to level-2 customers who develops non-secure code only. - In this scenario, or easy of development, Level-I customer releases the part to always allow non-secure debug. - To allow level-2 customers to further seal the part DCFG_CC_SOCU_NS is used. - ROM will use this word to further restrict the debug access.

bit_field.name: NIDEN
bit_field.description: Non Secure non-invasive debug fixed state

bit_field.name: CPU1_DBGEN
bit_field.description: CPU1 (Micro cortex M33) invasive debug fixed state

bit_field.name: ME_CMD_EN
bit_field.description: Flash Mass Erase Command fixed state

bit_field.name: CPU1_NIDEN
bit_field.description: CPU1 (Micro cortex M33) non-invasive debug fixed state

register.name: ENABLE_FA_MODE
register.description: Enable FA mode. SET_FA_MODE Command should write 0xC33CA55A to this word to indicate boot ROM to enter FA mode.

register.name: CMPA_PROG_IN_PROGRESS
register.description: CMPA Page programming on going. This field shall be set to 0x5CC55AA5 in the active CFPA page each time CMPA page programming is going on. It shall always be set to 0x00000000 in the CFPA scratch area.
